{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike visual semantic graphs, textual ones are not generated from the image itself but rather its caption.",
    "Specifically, the caption is parsed through the Stanford Dependency Parser [83], a widely used [84,85] probabilistic sentence parser.",
    "Given a caption, the parser will return its grammatical structure, identifying components such nouns, verbs, and adjectives and marking the relationship between them.",
    "This is then modified from a tree into a graph, following the techniques outlined in [86].Spatial graph.",
    "Yao et al. [39] define a spatial graph (Fig."
  ]
}